1. ${args2.description ? "Use the provided description" : "Ask the user: 'What do you want to accomplish?' (free text, not a form)"}
2. Convert description to kebab-case slug (max 40 chars)
3. ${projectStudio ? `Use studio "${projectStudio}"` : "Select studio per the logic above"}
4. Default to **continuous** mode (do not ask the user)
5. Summarize the conversation so far into a concise context block (key decisions, constraints, technical details discussed)
6. Call \`haiku_intent_create\` with description, slug, and the \`context\` argument containing your conversation summary
7. The tool creates directories, writes intent.md, writes CONVERSATION-CONTEXT.md to knowledge/, and opens a review for user confirmation
8. Invoke /haiku:run \u2014 the orchestrator opens the review and advances automatically (continuous) or report ready (discrete)`
        );
        const instructionText = contextParts.join("\n\n");
        if (args2.description) {
          return {
